## Key Takeaways

- HTTP traffic is not encrypted.
- HTTPS protects data using TLS encryption.
- Wireshark can recover files transmitted over HTTP.
- Export Objects is a valuable feature for forensic investigations.
- Security Analysts use this technique to investigate suspicious downloads and web activity.

